cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with developing saliency methods for visual explanations of network predictions, specifically for semantic segmentation networks. This involves exploring the potential of grid saliency to produce context explanations for dense prediction networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves developing and extending existing approaches, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with interpreting and detecting biases in data, which could fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
